WEBVTT

1
00:01:37.375 --> 00:01:39.666
<i>Let us know</i>
<i>when you're at the ops building. Over.</i>

2
00:01:50.458 --> 00:01:52.333
Six more months of your bullshit.

3
00:02:05.250 --> 00:02:08.208
I'm not…
I'm not trying to start problems with you.

4
00:02:08.291 --> 00:02:09.416
I'm just saying.

5
00:02:10.208 --> 00:02:11.250
No. I…

6
00:02:14.125 --> 00:02:17.125
All you had to do was wait six months.
and I would've been there to help.

7
00:02:24.666 --> 00:02:25.958
I got… I gotta go.

8
00:02:26.041 --> 00:02:28.458
But. listen. tomorrow
we can… we can figure this out.

9
00:02:28.541 --> 00:02:30.416
We can handle this whole situa…

10
00:02:31.666 --> 00:02:32.666
Hello?

11
00:02:33.458 --> 00:02:34.458
Hello?

12
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:47.750
Just coming on the shift?

13
00:02:49.833 --> 00:02:52.583
-Sergeant. you get my email?
-No. sir.

14
00:02:53.375 --> 00:02:55.708
Well. there's an update from the top

15
00:02:56.708 --> 00:02:57.916
for today

16
00:02:59.500 --> 00:03:01.166
of the utmost importance.

17
00:03:03.291 --> 00:03:04.291
That's an order.

18
00:03:05.291 --> 00:03:07.250
-All right. sir.
-Mm-hmm.

19
00:03:07.333 --> 00:03:09.041
Think you'll keep making that joke?

20
00:03:09.125 --> 00:03:11.083
If you keep smiling. I'll keep making it.

21
00:03:12.750 --> 00:03:13.875
I hope not.

22
00:03:23.083 --> 00:03:24.416
How'd that go?

23
00:03:25.666 --> 00:03:27.083
Still working on it.

24
00:03:27.916 --> 00:03:31.333
But we should have
some movement on it today. hopefully.

25
00:03:32.791 --> 00:03:35.541
-The regs say no food or drink.
-All right. man.

26
00:03:35.625 --> 00:03:36.958
If you want one. just ask.

27
00:03:45.125 --> 00:03:47.458
Break's every four hours.
Next time. you can wait.

28
00:03:47.541 --> 00:03:51.250
- What's up your ass. man?
- And clean up your workstation.

29
00:03:52.208 --> 00:03:54.416
It's covered in grease and chips and shit.

30
00:03:55.666 --> 00:03:56.666
Yes. sir.

31
00:04:07.291 --> 00:04:09.333
Look at the dinosaur coming in the way.

32
00:04:09.833 --> 00:04:11.166
Wow. Aw.

33
00:04:13.083 --> 00:04:15.958
- Guys. guys. it's 3:30 in the morning.
- I'm sorry.

34
00:04:16.750 --> 00:04:17.916
- Hi.
- Hi.

35
00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:19.708
How you feeling. conductor?

36
00:04:20.791 --> 00:04:22.666
- Mmm.
- How's he doing?

37
00:04:22.750 --> 00:04:25.333
Fever's gone up to 102.

38
00:04:25.416 --> 00:04:26.708
Oh gosh.

39
00:04:26.791 --> 00:04:29.500
-Come on. Let's get some shut-eye.
-Go to Daddy.

40
00:04:29.583 --> 00:04:31.166
- Come on.
- I love you.

41
00:04:31.250 --> 00:04:32.333
- Okay.
- I love you.

42
00:04:32.416 --> 00:04:34.333
I love you. Mommy's got her phone.

43
00:04:34.916 --> 00:04:35.875
What?

44
00:04:35.958 --> 00:04:38.125
- I can have him?
- Mm-hmm.

45
00:04:38.208 --> 00:04:39.666
- He's with me today?
- Mm-hmm.

46
00:04:39.750 --> 00:04:40.916
Thank you.

47
00:04:42.916 --> 00:04:44.208
-I love you.
-I love you too.

48
00:04:44.291 --> 00:04:45.500
I love you.

49
00:04:45.583 --> 00:04:49.000
-You wearing that to the White House?
-Yeah. It's. uh. Casual Friday today.

50
00:04:49.083 --> 00:04:50.583
- Thought so.
- Bye.

51
00:05:18.208 --> 00:05:19.208
<i>Babe…</i>

52
00:05:21.666 --> 00:05:22.750
<i>I love you.</i>

53
00:05:44.875 --> 00:05:46.291
- Good morning. ma'am.
- Morning.

54
00:05:46.791 --> 00:05:48.875
How are you. sir?
Can I see your badge. please?

55
00:05:50.416 --> 00:05:51.625
Thank you very much.

56
00:05:52.375 --> 00:05:53.458
Have a good shift.

57
00:05:59.083 --> 00:06:00.083
Keys.

58
00:06:00.666 --> 00:06:02.166
- Thank you. ma'am.
- Yeah.

59
00:06:21.208 --> 00:06:22.875
-Morning.
-Morning.

60
00:06:33.708 --> 00:06:36.208
- Here you go. sir. Thank you.
- Thank you. sir.

61
00:06:36.291 --> 00:06:37.375
-Morning. Captain.
-Morning.

62
00:06:37.458 --> 00:06:39.000
Um. egg-white omelet. please.

63
00:06:39.791 --> 00:06:41.166
- Usual?
- Yeah. thanks.

64
00:06:42.375 --> 00:06:45.625
-So when did you start?
-Last week. How did you--

65
00:06:45.708 --> 00:06:49.500
Egg sandwich or oatmeal.
Anything else holds up the line. Thanks.

66
00:07:14.416 --> 00:07:15.583
-Morning.
-Good morning.

67
00:07:17.916 --> 00:07:19.666
- How's it going. man?
- Morning.

68
00:07:22.875 --> 00:07:24.375
- Good morning.
- Morning.

69
00:07:32.041 --> 00:07:33.500
- Morning.
- Good morning.

70
00:07:34.083 --> 00:07:36.583
- Quiet night.
- For you. maybe.

71
00:07:36.666 --> 00:07:39.375
- You're kidding. Little guy again?
- He'll be fine.

72
00:07:39.458 --> 00:07:41.791
- PLA exercise in an hour.
- Really?

73
00:07:41.875 --> 00:07:44.333
I thought they'd call it off
and try and lower the temperature.

74
00:07:44.416 --> 00:07:46.708
I guess they like it hot.

75
00:07:48.208 --> 00:07:51.583
- Right. anything from Pyongyang?
- Not since the last test.

76
00:07:52.208 --> 00:07:55.000
Saber-rattling or silence.
I'm not sure which worries me more.

77
00:07:55.083 --> 00:07:56.291
Well. add to it.

78
00:07:56.375 --> 00:07:59.541
NSA is itchy about an uptick in chatter
between Tehran and their proxies.

79
00:07:59.625 --> 00:08:03.708
- They want it flagged in the Morning Book.
- Consider their asses covered.

80
00:08:04.541 --> 00:08:05.666
What's that?

81
00:08:05.750 --> 00:08:08.416
Butte County.
Over 100.000 homes at risk.

82
00:08:08.500 --> 00:08:09.833
That is not the feed.

83
00:08:09.916 --> 00:08:12.208
Same monitor was acting up yesterday.
We called systems.

84
00:08:12.291 --> 00:08:13.791
- Great. Bye.
- See you. Olivia.

85
00:08:13.875 --> 00:08:15.291
Hope the boy feels better.

86
00:08:15.375 --> 00:08:16.375
Sleep well.

87
00:08:17.208 --> 00:08:18.208
Oh!

88
00:08:18.291 --> 00:08:19.291
All right. Cheers.

89
00:08:19.375 --> 00:08:20.958
Cheers. Thank you.

90
00:08:23.916 --> 00:08:26.166
- Petty Officer Davis.
- Morning. ma'am.

91
00:08:26.250 --> 00:08:28.000
- Status update?
- On?

92
00:08:28.083 --> 00:08:29.916
Operation Don't Fuck This Up.

93
00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:32.500
I'm picking up
the ring tonight.

94
00:08:32.583 --> 00:08:34.958
Bravo Zulu. sailor.
That took you long enough.

95
00:08:36.458 --> 00:08:38.458
- Right. morning. everyone.
- Morning.

96
00:08:38.541 --> 00:08:40.708
Book push is two hours.
Let's get to it.

97
00:08:40.791 --> 00:08:42.416
- You got it.
- You got it.

98
00:09:02.916 --> 00:09:03.916
Rogers.

99
00:09:04.458 --> 00:09:09.375
No. He says the prenup is ironclad.
Those are the words he used.

100
00:09:10.291 --> 00:09:13.000
Well. I don't have time.
I don't have time to find another lawyer.

101
00:09:13.083 --> 00:09:14.916
Not if I wanna keep my job.

102
00:09:15.833 --> 00:09:18.625
Uh. I have to go. Goodbye. Thank you.

103
00:09:29.333 --> 00:09:33.041
At 0930. the president visits
a WNBA clinic for kids.

104
00:09:33.125 --> 00:09:35.333
Then we have the signing
of the Defense Omnibus bill

105
00:09:35.416 --> 00:09:36.958
with Hill leaders in the Roosevelt Room.

106
00:09:37.041 --> 00:09:40.958
We are pool for that.
Then three hours of executive time.

107
00:09:42.125 --> 00:09:42.958
Uh…

108
00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:47.000
…and the new Irish ambassador
is expected to stop by around 1600.

109
00:09:47.083 --> 00:09:48.958
so there may be an Oval spray.

110
00:09:49.041 --> 00:09:52.000
- And after that. it is a full lid.
<i>- Thanks. Abby.</i>

111
00:09:52.083 --> 00:09:53.166
{\an8}<i>Courtney's source at the UN</i>

112
00:09:53.250 --> 00:09:55.833
{\an8}<i>says the White House may push</i>
<i>for more sanctions on Moscow.</i>

113
00:09:55.916 --> 00:09:58.166
{\an8}I haven't heard that yet.

114
00:09:58.250 --> 00:10:00.916
but. um. I will ask around.

115
00:10:14.250 --> 00:10:16.000
Uh. we got a quick alert. sir.

116
00:10:16.083 --> 00:10:17.500
- Quick alert.
- Alert.

117
00:10:17.583 --> 00:10:19.250
- From where?
- Pacific.

118
00:10:20.958 --> 00:10:22.833
SBX1 detects a ballistic launch.

119
00:10:22.916 --> 00:10:24.875
Confirm track. Yes. sir. we're seeing it.

120
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:26.625
- Track on scope.
- Acknowledged.

121
00:10:26.708 --> 00:10:30.083
Vector 42.710. 137.14.

122
00:10:30.166 --> 00:10:35.250
Launch azimuth. 9.25 degrees.
Elevation angle. 66.79 degrees.

123
00:10:35.333 --> 00:10:37.166
Stand by for possible intercept.

124
00:10:37.250 --> 00:10:38.250
Copy that.

125
00:10:38.791 --> 00:10:41.333
- Right. log the time.
- Time is 0933.

126
00:10:41.416 --> 00:10:43.500
Initiate a national security
conference call.

127
00:10:43.583 --> 00:10:44.541
Copy.

128
00:10:44.625 --> 00:10:46.750
Patching in. and I am live.

129
00:10:46.833 --> 00:10:48.041
What's going on?

130
00:10:48.125 --> 00:10:50.208
STRATCOM's tracking a launch
over the Pacific.

131
00:10:51.333 --> 00:10:52.666
Second time since Christmas.

132
00:10:52.750 --> 00:10:54.458
- Uh. third.
- Right.

133
00:10:56.583 --> 00:10:58.166
Quarterly reviews. I was drowning.

134
00:10:58.250 --> 00:11:01.083
So give me a shoutout
if the world's going to end.

135
00:11:01.166 --> 00:11:04.041
- Yep.
- Yes. sir. Mr. Chairman. Adding you now.

136
00:11:11.916 --> 00:11:12.916
Point of origin?

137
00:11:15.541 --> 00:11:17.291
Lieutenant. point of origin?

138
00:11:17.375 --> 00:11:19.291
STRATCOM says indeterminate.

139
00:11:19.375 --> 00:11:22.083
DSP satellites missed the launch.
Floating rig picked it up.

140
00:11:22.791 --> 00:11:24.083
DSP missed the launch?

141
00:11:24.166 --> 00:11:26.833
Doesn't matter who launched it.
Just that we knock it down.

142
00:11:26.916 --> 00:11:29.541
Doesn't look like we'll have to.
TPY-2 Japan reports

143
00:11:29.625 --> 00:11:32.125
flight vector is consistent
with previous DPRK tests.

144
00:11:32.208 --> 00:11:34.375
Hmm. Another yo-yo.

145
00:11:35.291 --> 00:11:37.750
Winslow's crew was on
when the last one popped up.

146
00:11:37.833 --> 00:11:40.125
Said they were filling out paperwork
for a week.

147
00:11:41.875 --> 00:11:43.916
Uh. Mrs. Holland? This is the whizzer.

148
00:11:45.083 --> 00:11:48.125
Sorry. ma'am. Chief Petty Officer Davis.
White House Situation Room.

149
00:11:48.208 --> 00:11:49.500
Is your husband available?

150
00:11:52.916 --> 00:11:55.166
{\an8}<i>-Did you see that ball game last night?</i>
<i>-Yes. sir.</i>

151
00:11:55.250 --> 00:11:58.333
{\an8}- Okay. Yes. Thank you. ma'am.
<i>- You believe that Lindor?</i>

152
00:11:58.916 --> 00:12:00.000
<i>Impressive.</i>

153
00:12:00.083 --> 00:12:03.125
Apparently. the national security advisor
took a healthy hit of propofol.

154
00:12:03.208 --> 00:12:05.000
- Oh. Lucky him.
- Colonoscopy.

155
00:12:05.083 --> 00:12:06.416
- Call the deputy.
<i>- Morning.</i>

156
00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:09.750
<i>-Pleasure to see you. You ready?</i>
<i>-Where the hell's Holland?</i>

157
00:12:10.583 --> 00:12:11.958
Dr. Holland's indisposed. sir.

158
00:12:12.041 --> 00:12:15.791
but we've got Deputy National Security
Advisor Baerington with us.

159
00:12:15.875 --> 00:12:18.166
-He'll be with you shortly.
<i>-It'll be over by then.</i>

160
00:12:18.250 --> 00:12:20.458
<i>-I'm gonna start.</i>
<i>-Go ahead. Tony.</i>

161
00:12:20.541 --> 00:12:24.958
{\an8}<i>Approximately three minutes ago.</i>
<i>we detected an ICBM over the Pacific.</i>

162
00:12:25.041 --> 00:12:29.000
{\an8}<i>At this time. we haven't determined</i>
<i>if the launch was land or sea-based.</i>

163
00:12:29.500 --> 00:12:33.083
<i>but the object's trajectory</i>
<i>is consistent with previous tests.</i>

164
00:12:33.166 --> 00:12:36.666
<i>and we expect splashdown</i>
<i>somewhere in the Sea of Japan.</i>

165
00:12:48.041 --> 00:12:50.083
- Greely Ops Center.
- Greely Ops Center.

166
00:12:50.166 --> 00:12:51.500
Stand by. We're confirming.

167
00:12:51.583 --> 00:12:53.208
- Lieutenant Collins.
- Yes.

168
00:12:54.083 --> 00:12:55.166
Greely Ops Center.

169
00:12:55.250 --> 00:12:56.708
Where are we starting out now?

170
00:12:56.791 --> 00:12:59.166
- Sensor operator.
- Sergeant Diaz here.

171
00:13:01.416 --> 00:13:04.458
- We're connected to STRATCOM?
- Yeah. looks like another test.

172
00:13:04.541 --> 00:13:06.541
Greely Ops Center. Sergeant…

173
00:13:07.791 --> 00:13:09.041
What is it. Sergeant?

174
00:13:09.541 --> 00:13:12.291
Uh. clear radar acquired our object. sir.

175
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:14.875
Wait. And?

176
00:13:14.958 --> 00:13:18.083
Uh. rate of ascent slowing.
Inclination is flattening.

177
00:13:18.166 --> 00:13:19.416
Velocity?

178
00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:22.500
It's steady. sir.
Six kilometers per second.

179
00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:25.000
Wait. Is Cheyenne Mountain seeing this?

180
00:13:26.791 --> 00:13:29.375
Are you kidding?
This guy's big break. He's out for a walk?

181
00:13:29.458 --> 00:13:31.333
- A block away.
- Not good enough.

182
00:13:31.416 --> 00:13:33.250
Guys. let's keep working
the phones. everyone.

183
00:13:33.333 --> 00:13:34.458
If it is another test.

184
00:13:34.541 --> 00:13:37.541
I want a note within the hour
summarizing regional reaction.

185
00:13:37.625 --> 00:13:38.458
Aye. Captain.

186
00:13:38.541 --> 00:13:40.166
- You better get back on.
- Yep.

187
00:13:40.875 --> 00:13:43.000
<i>Sorry about that. Seems we have an update.</i>

188
00:13:44.458 --> 00:13:46.666
{\an8}<i>Current velocity indicates</i>

189
00:13:47.166 --> 00:13:49.791
{\an8}<i>that the object will go suborbital.</i>

190
00:13:51.916 --> 00:13:53.708
{\an8}<i>Current flight trajectory is consistent</i>

191
00:13:53.791 --> 00:13:56.708
{\an8}<i>with impact somewhere</i>
<i>in the continental United States.</i>

192
00:13:56.791 --> 00:13:58.083
<i>Holy shit.</i>

193
00:14:00.041 --> 00:14:02.583
<i>What's your level of confidence</i>
<i>on that. Tony?</i>

194
00:14:03.875 --> 00:14:07.958
<i>Not an error. We're tracking it</i>
<i>on multiple radar systems now.</i>

195
00:14:08.625 --> 00:14:12.833
<i>I'm told… Hi. Jerry.</i>
<i>…we have dual phenomenology on the track.</i>

196
00:14:13.333 --> 00:14:15.166
<i>Nineteen minutes to impact.</i>

197
00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:21.791
Ma'am. I… I don't understand.

198
00:14:23.708 --> 00:14:25.666
Add SECDEF and POTUS to the call.

199
00:14:26.291 --> 00:14:27.833
Now. Davis.

200
00:14:28.416 --> 00:14:30.083
- Were you listening to that?
- I was.

201
00:14:30.166 --> 00:14:31.708
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Get to it.

202
00:14:34.875 --> 00:14:36.416
Check the shot doctrine.

203
00:14:36.500 --> 00:14:37.916
State Department. yeah.

204
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:39.125
Repeat that to me.

205
00:14:39.666 --> 00:14:41.500
-Authenticate.
-Uh…

206
00:14:42.666 --> 00:14:43.791
Uh…

207
00:14:45.125 --> 00:14:46.166
- Uh…
- Here. Here.

208
00:14:46.250 --> 00:14:50.000
Oscar. Foxtrot. four. niner. one. six.

209
00:14:50.083 --> 00:14:52.666
Sergeant. you're doing fine.
We've trained for this a million times.

210
00:14:52.750 --> 00:14:53.791
You're good.

211
00:14:53.875 --> 00:14:57.083
Oscar. Foxtrot. four. nine. one. six.
Order is authentic.

212
00:14:59.541 --> 00:15:00.833
I'm sorry. say again.

213
00:15:07.708 --> 00:15:10.375
{\an8}We have weapons-release authority
to launch our GBIs.

214
00:15:15.666 --> 00:15:17.250
Confirm DEFCON 2.

215
00:15:17.833 --> 00:15:18.875
Holy shit.

216
00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:22.958
- Down to two.
- Currently. we are at DEFCON 2.

217
00:15:24.041 --> 00:15:27.500
- Are you looking at this?
- DEFCON 2. I repeat. DEFCON 2.

218
00:15:27.583 --> 00:15:29.916
- Have we seen DEFCON 2 before?
- No.

219
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:33.416
Hey. I know this isn't my business.
but it seems really serious.

220
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:35.208
I'm sorry.
I can't give you any information.

221
00:15:35.291 --> 00:15:39.583
Everyone. relax. okay? A rounding error.

222
00:15:39.666 --> 00:15:42.083
This is still
a commercial satellite launch.

223
00:15:42.166 --> 00:15:45.916
Some billionaire forgot to file
the right paperwork. send his email.

224
00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:46.833
Okay. focus.

225
00:15:46.916 --> 00:15:49.416
POTUS is on campus.
Mr. Watts has been notified.

226
00:15:49.500 --> 00:15:51.041
-Adding SECDEF now.
-Great.

227
00:15:51.125 --> 00:15:53.208
SIGINT indicates Moscow
is aware of the launch.

228
00:15:53.291 --> 00:15:57.500
Atypical DPRK activity along the DMZ
could be an unannounced rotation.

229
00:15:57.583 --> 00:15:58.833
but they're not picking up.

230
00:15:58.916 --> 00:16:00.333
Could this be the PLA exercise?

231
00:16:00.416 --> 00:16:03.000
Maybe Davis staged it
so he could put off proposing?

232
00:16:03.083 --> 00:16:06.041
-Hey. not now.
-Exercise was surface warfare only.

233
00:16:06.125 --> 00:16:06.958
No SSBNs.

234
00:16:07.041 --> 00:16:10.500
USS Ford reports multiple J-15s
now launching from the Fujian.

235
00:16:10.583 --> 00:16:13.166
-We expect that?
-We ever know what the Chinese are doing?

236
00:16:14.208 --> 00:16:15.041
Huh?

237
00:16:15.541 --> 00:16:17.833
I mean. a car just backfired.
People are spooked.

238
00:16:18.333 --> 00:16:20.000
I'd be more worried if they weren't.

239
00:16:20.666 --> 00:16:21.750
