940
01:01:08.375 --> 01:01:13.041
Jesus Christ. I got action in Khorramabad.
Sirens in Tel Aviv. sir.

941
01:01:13.125 --> 01:01:14.958
Everybody knows we missed.

942
01:01:16.666 --> 01:01:19.583
Mr. President. we're seeing
some concerning activity

943
01:01:19.666 --> 01:01:21.666
from our adversaries
on a number of fronts.

944
01:01:21.750 --> 01:01:24.083
<i>More concerning</i>
<i>than a goddamn nuclear launch?</i>

945
01:01:24.166 --> 01:01:29.000
Sir. the USS Virginia reports
it's just lost contact with its shadow.

946
01:01:29.083 --> 01:01:32.708
one of four Russian submarines
we're tracking in the North Atlantic.

947
01:01:32.791 --> 01:01:36.333
each presumably armed with 16 SLBMs.

948
01:01:36.416 --> 01:01:39.375
Until we know differently.
we have to assume this may get worse.

949
01:01:39.458 --> 01:01:43.000
{\an8}<i>General Brady. I know</i>
<i>everyone's trying to do their jobs here.</i>

950
01:01:43.541 --> 01:01:45.250
{\an8}<i>but we need to slow the fuck down.</i>

951
01:01:46.375 --> 01:01:47.625
<i>President's right.</i>

952
01:01:47.708 --> 01:01:49.833
There's no way
he can make an informed decision

953
01:01:49.916 --> 01:01:51.333
under these circumstances.

954
01:01:51.416 --> 01:01:53.791
<i>Mr. President. Mr. Baerington.</i>

955
01:01:53.875 --> 01:01:57.000
<i>slowing down is one luxury</i>
<i>we just don't have.</i>

956
01:01:57.708 --> 01:01:59.625
These are the circumstances.

957
01:01:59.708 --> 01:02:03.833
In little more than seven minutes.
we will lose the city of Chicago.

958
01:02:03.916 --> 01:02:05.750
I can't tell you why.

959
01:02:06.458 --> 01:02:09.833
Or why we're seeing
North Korea. Russia. China.

960
01:02:09.916 --> 01:02:13.458
Pakistan. and even Iran
raising their alerts

961
01:02:13.541 --> 01:02:16.875
and mobilizing their forces
across air. land. and sea.

962
01:02:18.083 --> 01:02:20.916
Perhaps. as Mr. Baerington
suggested earlier.

963
01:02:21.000 --> 01:02:24.833
<i>they are simply and innocently</i>
<i>responding to our posture.</i>

964
01:02:24.916 --> 01:02:26.416
<i>It is also possible</i>

965
01:02:26.500 --> 01:02:30.833
<i>that they've seen our homeland</i>
<i>is about to absorb a catastrophic blow.</i>

966
01:02:30.916 --> 01:02:33.500
<i>and they are readying</i>
<i>to take advantage of that.</i>

967
01:02:33.583 --> 01:02:37.333
Or this is all part of
a phased. coordinated assault.

968
01:02:37.416 --> 01:02:38.833
with far worse to come.

969
01:02:38.916 --> 01:02:40.416
I simply don't know.

970
01:02:40.500 --> 01:02:42.791
What I do know is this.

971
01:02:42.875 --> 01:02:48.375
If we do not take steps
to neutralize our enemies now.

972
01:02:48.458 --> 01:02:51.125
we will lose our window to do so.

973
01:02:51.208 --> 01:02:53.375
<i>We can strike preemptively.</i>

974
01:02:53.458 --> 01:02:57.333
<i>or risk 100 ICBMs launching our way.</i>

975
01:02:57.416 --> 01:03:01.083
at which time.
this war will have already been lost.

976
01:03:05.875 --> 01:03:07.375
{\an8}<i>And if there is no war?</i>

977
01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:10.833
<i>If this is it?</i>

978
01:03:10.916 --> 01:03:13.958
I think we'd all welcome
any indication of that.

979
01:03:14.041 --> 01:03:17.375
{\an8}As unfathomable as it was
just five minutes ago.

980
01:03:17.458 --> 01:03:19.666
{\an8}I'd accept the loss
of ten million Americans

981
01:03:19.750 --> 01:03:22.833
{\an8}if I could be absolutely certain
it stops there.

982
01:03:22.916 --> 01:03:27.250
Of course. in absence of that certainty.
we can all certainly say a prayer

983
01:03:27.333 --> 01:03:31.750
{\an8}and rely on the goodwill
of our adversaries to keep us safe.

984
01:03:31.833 --> 01:03:36.416
{\an8}Or we can hit their command centers.
silos. and bombers

985
01:03:36.500 --> 01:03:38.291
while they're still on the ground.

986
01:03:38.375 --> 01:03:42.333
eliminating their ability
to take further action against us.

987
01:03:44.666 --> 01:03:47.833
We've already lost
one American city today.

988
01:03:49.333 --> 01:03:50.625
How many more do you wanna risk?

989
01:03:50.708 --> 01:03:52.333
<i>What kind of question is that?</i>

990
01:03:53.625 --> 01:03:56.416
<i>-This is insanity. okay?</i>
-No. sir.

991
01:03:58.458 --> 01:03:59.958
This is reality.

992
01:04:00.541 --> 01:04:01.833
Six minutes to impact.

993
01:04:01.916 --> 01:04:05.208
It's Walker. She's got
the Russian foreign minister on the line.

994
01:04:05.291 --> 01:04:06.791
We can't merge the calls.

995
01:04:09.250 --> 01:04:10.250
Jake.

996
01:04:10.916 --> 01:04:12.958
Sit room has
the Russian foreign minister on the line.

997
01:04:13.041 --> 01:04:15.000
but we cannot merge the call.

998
01:04:15.750 --> 01:04:18.500
You need to pick up and take it.

999
01:04:19.791 --> 01:04:21.625
It has to be you.

1000
01:04:23.208 --> 01:04:24.208
Okay?

1001
01:04:24.833 --> 01:04:28.333
The president needs a reason
not to retaliate. okay? You give him one.

1002
01:04:31.083 --> 01:04:32.416
-You ready?
-Yeah.

1003
01:04:33.083 --> 01:04:34.250
Let's go.

1004
01:04:35.541 --> 01:04:37.458
This is Jake Baerington.

1005
01:04:37.541 --> 01:04:41.208
- I'm the deputy national security advisor.
<i>- You authorized to speak?</i>

1006
01:04:41.291 --> 01:04:44.583
I'm authorized to do whatever's necessary
to de-escalate this situation. sir.

1007
01:04:44.666 --> 01:04:48.875
<i>Your bombers are airborne.</i>
<i>What kind of de-escalation is that?</i>

1008
01:04:48.958 --> 01:04:50.291
Mr. Foreign Minister.

1009
01:04:50.375 --> 01:04:52.708
you have to understand
that's only a precaution.

1010
01:04:53.583 --> 01:04:55.458
Okay. our country is about to be hit

1011
01:04:55.541 --> 01:04:58.708
by an entirely unprecedented
and unprovoked attack.

1012
01:04:58.791 --> 01:05:00.875
<i>Which we</i>
<i>had nothing to do with.</i>

1013
01:05:00.958 --> 01:05:02.333
Do I have your word?

1014
01:05:02.416 --> 01:05:05.333
Can I assure the president
that Russia has nothing to do with this.

1015
01:05:05.416 --> 01:05:08.625
<i>they're not behind the launch.</i>
<i>and you will not seek to capitalize?</i>

1016
01:05:08.708 --> 01:05:09.708
Yes.

1017
01:05:10.541 --> 01:05:11.875
And do I have your word

1018
01:05:12.541 --> 01:05:15.875
that you won't use it as an excuse
to wipe us out?

1019
01:05:15.958 --> 01:05:18.166
- That's ridiculous.
<i>- Is it?</i>

1020
01:05:18.250 --> 01:05:19.708
<i>You might tell your president.</i>

1021
01:05:19.791 --> 01:05:24.458
<i>if your forces do not stand down.</i>
<i>we will be compelled to respond in kind.</i>

1022
01:05:25.250 --> 01:05:28.083
You have a sub off our coast
that just slipped its shadow.

1023
01:05:28.166 --> 01:05:31.208
<i>Order it to the surface</i>
<i>to identify its location</i>

1024
01:05:31.291 --> 01:05:32.625
<i>as a show of good faith.</i>

1025
01:05:32.708 --> 01:05:34.791
So you can wipe it out of the water?

1026
01:05:34.875 --> 01:05:37.333
We are running out of time.

1027
01:05:37.416 --> 01:05:39.083
and my wife is six months…

1028
01:05:41.666 --> 01:05:42.666
<i>Jake.</i>

1029
01:05:42.750 --> 01:05:44.458
I'm sorry. Um…

1030
01:05:46.500 --> 01:05:47.750
Jake?

1031
01:05:47.833 --> 01:05:49.625
<i>Listen. if we get this wrong.</i>

1032
01:05:50.458 --> 01:05:52.458
none of us are gonna be alive tomorrow.

1033
01:05:52.541 --> 01:05:55.125
Now. if you're telling me
that you didn't do this.

1034
01:05:55.208 --> 01:05:56.541
<i>and I believe you.</i>

1035
01:05:56.625 --> 01:05:59.541
<i>then I can promise you</i>
<i>we will not hit any Russian targets.</i>

1036
01:05:59.625 --> 01:06:03.958
<i>Can you promise me you will stand down</i>
<i>your long-range strategic assets?</i>

1037
01:06:04.041 --> 01:06:06.958
<i>Better.</i>
<i>There'll be no retaliation at all.</i>

1038
01:06:07.041 --> 01:06:08.125
I completely agree.

1039
01:06:08.208 --> 01:06:11.208
<i>And I will push for that.</i>
<i>but that is not my decision. sir.</i>

1040
01:06:11.291 --> 01:06:13.208
If you do retaliate.

1041
01:06:13.291 --> 01:06:18.000
can you guarantee that your response
will not infringe on our airspace?

1042
01:06:22.583 --> 01:06:25.000
With our bombers.
yes. of course.

1043
01:06:25.083 --> 01:06:26.333
And missiles?

1044
01:06:26.416 --> 01:06:29.916
If you determine that. God.
fucking China is responsible--

1045
01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:32.083
- Sir. there…
- Tell the truth.

1046
01:06:32.791 --> 01:06:33.625
No.

1047
01:06:37.125 --> 01:06:39.666
Sir. we both know
that there would be some overflight.

1048
01:06:39.750 --> 01:06:41.166
<i>There's no way around that.</i>

1049
01:06:41.250 --> 01:06:43.916
And you expect us
to simply trust

1050
01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:47.250
that warheads flying over our head
are not destined on our cities?

1051
01:06:47.333 --> 01:06:50.041
<i>Hopefully. sir.</i>
<i>there will not be any warheads.</i>

1052
01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:55.541
If there are. then. yes.
I'm asking you to trust me.

1053
01:06:59.458 --> 01:07:00.666
Trust.

1054
01:07:01.708 --> 01:07:02.666
Why?

1055
01:07:04.083 --> 01:07:06.250
<i>-I'll talk to my president.</i>
-What if. um--

1056
01:07:14.208 --> 01:07:15.875
<i>Darkstar. this is Ghost 1.</i>

1057
01:07:15.958 --> 01:07:17.625
Approaching loiter position.

1058
01:07:19.500 --> 01:07:21.750
<i>Ghost 1-1. Darkstar.</i>
<i>Picture clean.</i>

1059
01:07:21.833 --> 01:07:23.458
<i>Stand by mission data package.</i>

1060
01:07:31.083 --> 01:07:32.666
Is this right?

1061
01:07:33.625 --> 01:07:35.833
Darkstar. Ghost. MDB confirmed.

1062
01:07:37.791 --> 01:07:40.333
<i>Ghost. Darkstar.</i>
<i>Stand by execution order.</i>

1063
01:07:42.708 --> 01:07:45.250
Forward-deployed B-2s
are at loitering position.

1064
01:07:45.333 --> 01:07:47.833
Mr. President.
we're going to need your decision.

1065
01:07:48.333 --> 01:07:51.750
Lieutenant Commander Reeves
is your strike advisor

1066
01:07:52.250 --> 01:07:55.500
and can walk you through
the authentication process.

1067
01:07:55.583 --> 01:07:59.000
Then you'll need to read aloud
an attack option designation--

1068
01:07:59.083 --> 01:08:01.500
<i>Yeah. Look.</i>
<i>I understand all that. all right?</i>

1069
01:08:01.583 --> 01:08:03.708
<i>Reid. I need you.</i>

1070
01:08:05.583 --> 01:08:06.833
<i>What do you think. Reid?</i>

1071
01:08:06.916 --> 01:08:08.708
<i>We're close to take off.</i>

1072
01:08:08.791 --> 01:08:10.000
<i>Did we lose him?</i>

1073
01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:12.541
{\an8}<i>Sir! No. no. no. no. sir!</i>

1074
01:08:13.041 --> 01:08:14.833
{\an8}<i>Holy shit!</i>

1075
01:08:15.416 --> 01:08:16.916
- <i>What was that?</i>
- All right.

1076
01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:18.541
<i>Mr. President?</i>

1077
01:08:18.625 --> 01:08:21.375
<i>-It's Jake again. sir. Baerington.</i>
-Keep your seats. Keep your seats.

1078
01:08:21.458 --> 01:08:23.500
{\an8}<i>I spoke</i>
<i>to the Russian foreign minister.</i>

1079
01:08:23.583 --> 01:08:26.958
He denies their responsibility
for the launch.

1080
01:08:27.625 --> 01:08:30.750
Said he spoke to Beijing.
and he doesn't think it was them either.

1081
01:08:33.416 --> 01:08:35.916
- I believed him. sir.
<i>- You did?</i>

1082
01:08:36.500 --> 01:08:39.666
<i>-They gonna back down?</i>
-Sir. I think that they want to.

1083
01:08:40.750 --> 01:08:43.416
And if we can guarantee
that we will not retaliate.

1084
01:08:43.500 --> 01:08:44.875
I think I can. uh…

1085
01:08:46.416 --> 01:08:48.416
we can convince them.

1086
01:08:48.500 --> 01:08:51.041
- <i>What does that mean?</i>
<i>- We don't launch.</i>

1087
01:08:51.958 --> 01:08:53.250
<i>Against anyone.</i>

1088
01:08:53.916 --> 01:08:55.000
<i>For now. at least.</i>

1089
01:08:55.083 --> 01:08:57.833
<i>What. we just sit back</i>
<i>and watch Chicago incinerate?</i>

1090
01:08:58.375 --> 01:09:01.666
{\an8}<i>Are you fucking kidding me? Do you think</i>
<i>the American people are gonna go for that?</i>

1091
01:09:01.750 --> 01:09:04.625
<i>Sir. the… the warhead.</i>
<i>it might still malfunction.</i>

1092
01:09:04.708 --> 01:09:06.333
<i>They do that sometimes.</i>

1093
01:09:06.416 --> 01:09:08.666
<i>Did he agree to these terms?</i>

1094
01:09:09.166 --> 01:09:12.291
<i>All right. we do nothing.</i>
<i>they back off for certain?</i>

1095
01:09:12.375 --> 01:09:14.375
- More or less.
<i>- More or less?!</i>

1096
01:09:14.458 --> 01:09:15.875
<i>- Jake.</i>
<i>- Yes. sir.</i>

1097
01:09:15.958 --> 01:09:17.833
<i>I'm gonna need you to breathe.</i>

1098
01:09:17.916 --> 01:09:19.041
I'm breathing just fine. sir.

1099
01:09:19.125 --> 01:09:22.666
<i>Good 'cause my job is</i>
<i>to make this decision. I wish it weren't.</i>

1100
01:09:22.750 --> 01:09:26.375
<i>And your job is to tell me</i>
<i>exactly what he agreed to.</i>

1101
01:09:27.250 --> 01:09:30.166
<i>-No bullshit. Can you do that?</i>
-He didn't agree to anything. sir.

1102
01:09:30.250 --> 01:09:32.083
He said
he needed to speak with his president.

1103
01:09:32.583 --> 01:09:35.041
Sounds to me like we know nothing new.

1104
01:09:35.125 --> 01:09:37.833
<i>Wrong. General.</i>
<i>If we do what he's asking.</i>

1105
01:09:37.916 --> 01:09:40.000
<i>if we hold back.</i>
<i>there's at least a chance.</i>

1106
01:09:40.083 --> 01:09:41.541
Two minutes and 30 seconds.

1107
01:09:41.625 --> 01:09:44.583
<i>Jake. Jake.</i>
<i>I do what you're suggesting.</i>

1108
01:09:45.791 --> 01:09:48.041
<i>I let whoever did this get away with it.</i>

1109
01:09:48.541 --> 01:09:50.500
<i>How is that any different</i>
<i>from surrendering?</i>

1110
01:09:50.583 --> 01:09:52.541
<i>Sir. if you</i>
<i>wanna look at it that way.</i>

1111
01:09:53.166 --> 01:09:55.500
then I'm telling you your choices are

1112
01:09:55.583 --> 01:09:57.083
surrender or suicide.

1113
01:10:01.875 --> 01:10:03.000
Uh…

1114
01:10:08.333 --> 01:10:09.666
<i>We gonna need a minute.</i>

1115
01:10:11.833 --> 01:10:13.333
So what now? What are we doing?

1116
01:10:14.416 --> 01:10:16.041
Now I call Fort Belvoir.

1117
01:10:16.125 --> 01:10:18.666
Put the Army Corps of Engineers
on standby.

1118
01:10:19.666 --> 01:10:22.583
In case the White House gets hit
and they need to dig us out.

1119
01:10:22.666 --> 01:10:23.625
Oh God.

1120
01:10:23.708 --> 01:10:25.666
- Serious?
- That's the plan.

1121
01:10:27.583 --> 01:10:29.000
There's a plan for this?

1122
01:10:38.916 --> 01:10:40.375
If this order comes through…

1123
01:10:42.875 --> 01:10:44.375
I know my job. sir.

1124
01:11:00.166 --> 01:11:05.291
<i>Romeo. Bravo. Juliett. Whiskey.</i>
<i>Delta. Foxtrot. Echo.</i>

1125
01:11:05.375 --> 01:11:07.333
Missilization order is authentic.

1126
01:11:08.916 --> 01:11:10.500
Romeo. Bravo. Juliett.

1127
01:11:10.583 --> 01:11:13.125
Whiskey. Delta. Foxtrot. Echo.

1128
01:11:13.208 --> 01:11:14.583
I concur with missilization.

1129
01:11:15.666 --> 01:11:16.791
Three. two. one. Turn.

1130
01:11:16.875 --> 01:11:18.750
Sir. standing by for fire order.

1131
01:11:20.041 --> 01:11:22.083
Sir. your nuclear forces are ready.

1132
01:11:22.583 --> 01:11:24.791
- Sir. B-2s are at loiter.
- Yes. sir.

1133
01:11:24.875 --> 01:11:27.083
{\an8}Missile field status green.

1134
01:11:27.166 --> 01:11:28.916
{\an8}What if he doesn't come back on?

1135
01:11:30.541 --> 01:11:34.041
Decapitation event.
We find the vice president.

1136
01:11:34.125 --> 01:11:37.958
If we can't reach him. speaker.
Right on down the list.

1137
01:11:38.041 --> 01:11:39.166
<i>I'm here.</i>

1138
01:11:40.083 --> 01:11:42.916
- <i>You'll need your SAS card. sir.</i>
<i>- Oh.</i>

1139
01:11:45.708 --> 01:11:47.208
<i>It's in here somewhere.</i>

1140
01:11:48.041 --> 01:11:49.125
<i>Right.</i>

1141
01:11:50.041 --> 01:11:51.916
<i>Reminds me of when I was in college.</i>

1142
01:11:54.958 --> 01:11:57.208
<i>You just. uh. read it aloud.</i>

1143
01:11:59.708 --> 01:12:02.500
{\an8}<i>November. Delta. Oscar.</i>

1144
01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:06.000
{\an8}<i>One. one. one. seven.</i>

1145
01:12:06.083 --> 01:12:08.500
November. Delta. Oscar.

1146
01:12:08.583 --> 01:12:11.541
<i>One. one. one. seven.</i>

1147
01:12:13.333 --> 01:12:15.833
<i>National command authority confirmed.</i>

1148
01:12:17.625 --> 01:12:19.458
Your orders. Mr. President?

1149
01:12:20.208 --> 01:12:21.375
<i>My orders?</i>

1150
01:13:01.416 --> 01:13:03.708
You sure you
don't want any coffee? Water?

1151
01:13:04.208 --> 01:13:05.625
No. thank you. ma'am.

1152
01:13:21.875 --> 01:13:24.166
Betty. can you get us the majority leader?

1153
01:13:24.250 --> 01:13:26.750
Quickly. please. Thanks.

1154
01:13:28.708 --> 01:13:30.500
Already 45 minutes late.

1155
01:13:33.583 --> 01:13:35.416
POTUS for majority leader. please.

1156
01:13:36.500 --> 01:13:37.333
Thank you.

1157
01:14:02.916 --> 01:14:04.625
That's looking more like it.

1158
01:14:22.125 --> 01:14:23.208
Nope.

1159
01:14:23.791 --> 01:14:25.125
Out playing nine.

1160
01:14:26.583 --> 01:14:28.041
It's going. I guess.

1161
01:14:28.541 --> 01:14:31.958
Last time I was around all these uniforms.
I was a private.

1162
01:14:32.583 --> 01:14:34.500
They're still full of shit.

1163
01:14:40.458 --> 01:14:42.500
Thanks. George. I appreciate that.

