01:28:08.916 --> 01:28:11.125
- <i>We're good. man. I'm a slob.</i>
<i>- Six. Five…</i>

1391
01:28:11.208 --> 01:28:13.500
<i>To hell with her.</i>
<i>Shouldn't have left it like that.</i>

1392
01:28:14.083 --> 01:28:15.083
<i>Three.</i>

1393
01:28:15.583 --> 01:28:16.500
<i>Two.</i>

1394
01:28:17.583 --> 01:28:18.708
<i>One.</i>

1395
01:28:27.458 --> 01:28:30.625
<i>Confirm impact.</i>

1396
01:28:31.875 --> 01:28:34.125
- <i>Confirm impact.</i>
<i>- Stand by. Confirming.</i>

1397
01:28:37.541 --> 01:28:39.250
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>What are you waiting for?</i>

1398
01:28:42.458 --> 01:28:44.208
- <i>It's negative.</i>
<i>- What'd he say?</i>

1399
01:28:45.250 --> 01:28:46.333
<i>What'd he say?</i>

1400
01:28:47.666 --> 01:28:48.666
<i>I. uh…</i>

1401
01:28:49.375 --> 01:28:50.541
<i>A negative impact.</i>

1402
01:28:51.583 --> 01:28:53.083
<i>Object remains inbound.</i>

1403
01:29:01.791 --> 01:29:03.958
<i>We did every fucking thing right.</i>

1404
01:29:04.458 --> 01:29:07.416
<i>Mr. President.</i>
<i>confirming DEFCON 1. sir.</i>

1405
01:29:08.041 --> 01:29:10.500
<i>Oh Jesus. We just went DEFCON 1.</i>

1406
01:29:10.583 --> 01:29:12.708
- <i>Okay.</i>
<i>- Negative impact.</i>

1407
01:29:12.791 --> 01:29:13.833
Confirming.

1408
01:29:13.916 --> 01:29:15.041
Uh…

1409
01:29:20.666 --> 01:29:23.791
<i>Major. confirm the release</i>
<i>of two additional GBIs to intercept.</i>

1410
01:29:27.041 --> 01:29:28.708
Why the hell is that book out. son?

1411
01:29:28.791 --> 01:29:32.166
<i>Mr. President. significant time</i>
<i>and expertise were devoted</i>

1412
01:29:32.250 --> 01:29:33.958
<i>to designing these options.</i>

1413
01:29:34.041 --> 01:29:37.291
<i>You'll find a range.</i>
<i>select. limited. and major.</i>

1414
01:29:37.375 --> 01:29:40.208
<i>depending on the scale of the response</i>
<i>you feel is warranted.</i>

1415
01:29:40.291 --> 01:29:43.625
<i>I suggest you allow</i>
<i>Lieutenant Commander Reeves to brief you.</i>

1416
01:29:43.708 --> 01:29:47.583
Per the provisions
of OPLAN 8044. Revision 25.

1417
01:29:47.666 --> 01:29:51.000
the NMCC requests authority
to initiate a counterstrike.

1418
01:29:51.666 --> 01:29:53.791
The green tab are SAOs.

1419
01:29:53.875 --> 01:29:55.833
yellow. LAOs.

1420
01:29:55.916 --> 01:29:57.416
and red. MAOs.

1421
01:29:57.500 --> 01:30:00.500
Within each section.
your options are organized by region.

1422
01:30:00.583 --> 01:30:04.041
On each page.
you'll find a designation number.

1423
01:30:04.125 --> 01:30:06.666
both a map and a list of targets.

1424
01:30:07.291 --> 01:30:09.500
along with enemy casualty estimates.

1425
01:30:10.000 --> 01:30:11.750
Where would you like to begin. sir?

1426
01:30:12.625 --> 01:30:15.500
<i>Mr. President. we're seeing</i>
<i>some concerning activity</i>

1427
01:30:15.583 --> 01:30:17.583
<i>from our adversaries</i>
<i>on a number of fronts.</i>

1428
01:30:17.666 --> 01:30:20.291
More concerning
than a goddamn nuclear launch?

1429
01:30:20.375 --> 01:30:21.541
- <i>Please stop.</i>
- Carrie.

1430
01:30:21.625 --> 01:30:23.750
<i>-I told you. I need space.</i>
-I know. I…

1431
01:30:23.833 --> 01:30:25.708
- Where are you?
<i>- I'm not doing this now.</i>

1432
01:30:25.791 --> 01:30:27.541
Carrie. please.

1433
01:30:27.625 --> 01:30:29.750
<i>I'm home.</i>
<i>about to leave for rehearsal.</i>

1434
01:30:29.833 --> 01:30:31.833
<i>Look. can I call you later?</i>

1435
01:30:32.416 --> 01:30:34.958
My therapist actually thinks that…

1436
01:30:37.375 --> 01:30:40.375
I know we have to talk at some point.

1437
01:30:42.041 --> 01:30:45.500
With Mom. it's just been a lot. okay?

1438
01:30:46.125 --> 01:30:47.125
<i>I know.</i>

1439
01:30:49.458 --> 01:30:50.625
You coming. hon?

1440
01:30:51.291 --> 01:30:53.833
- Yeah. I'm coming. I have to go.
- We're gonna be late.

1441
01:30:53.916 --> 01:30:56.541
- <i>Who is that?</i>
- A friend.

1442
01:30:57.791 --> 01:30:59.416
I'm seeing someone.

1443
01:31:00.958 --> 01:31:02.875
- You are?
<i>- Yeah.</i>

1444
01:31:03.708 --> 01:31:05.208
Is it serious?

1445
01:31:05.291 --> 01:31:07.625
- <i>Come on.</i>
- Well. is it?

1446
01:31:08.916 --> 01:31:10.416
<i>Yeah. I think so.</i>

1447
01:31:12.208 --> 01:31:13.875
He's going with you to work?

1448
01:31:14.458 --> 01:31:16.541
<i>We walk together.</i>
<i>It's in the same direction.</i>

1449
01:31:20.083 --> 01:31:21.083
Good.

1450
01:31:22.250 --> 01:31:23.333
That's good.

1451
01:31:24.375 --> 01:31:27.500
You're being really strange.
I'll call you when I can. okay?

1452
01:31:28.083 --> 01:31:30.000
- <i>I love you. Carrie.</i>
- Goodbye. Dad.

1453
01:31:36.125 --> 01:31:37.125
Okay.

1454
01:31:41.041 --> 01:31:43.208
Sir. I insist that you leave.

1455
01:31:45.375 --> 01:31:47.208
Sir. sorry.
I've transferred the call.

1456
01:31:47.291 --> 01:31:48.500
You need to leave now.

1457
01:31:48.583 --> 01:31:50.166
Sir.

1458
01:31:58.208 --> 01:32:01.166
<i>We've already lost</i>
<i>one American city today.</i>

1459
01:32:02.708 --> 01:32:05.833
<i>-How many more do you wanna risk?</i>
-What kind of fucking question is that?

1460
01:32:07.625 --> 01:32:10.083
This is insanity. okay?

1461
01:32:10.166 --> 01:32:11.083
<i>No. sir.</i>

1462
01:32:13.125 --> 01:32:14.625
<i>This is reality.</i>

1463
01:32:15.166 --> 01:32:17.041
<i>Six minutes to impact.</i>

1464
01:32:19.083 --> 01:32:22.500
- What's your name?
- Lieutenant Commander Reeves. sir.

1465
01:32:24.208 --> 01:32:25.833
How old are you. man?

1466
01:32:25.916 --> 01:32:27.750
Uh. 32. sir.

1467
01:32:28.333 --> 01:32:29.583
Got a family?

1468
01:32:31.208 --> 01:32:32.625
I have a wife. sir.

1469
01:32:57.333 --> 01:32:58.708
Icon arriving.

1470
01:33:20.708 --> 01:33:23.000
Andrews tower.
Marine One taking off.

1471
01:33:34.375 --> 01:33:35.666
Eighty-nine targets.

1472
01:33:35.750 --> 01:33:39.125
mostly military installations
and leadership sites.

1473
01:33:39.208 --> 01:33:42.541
As of last month.
we have a B-2 squadron forward-deployed.

1474
01:33:42.625 --> 01:33:44.958
We'll also employ our Ohio-class subs.

1475
01:33:45.041 --> 01:33:49.375
each with 24 Trident II D5
MIRV-equipped ballistic missiles.

1476
01:33:50.083 --> 01:33:52.833
This option calls for
a dozen Minutemen as well. out of Warren.

1477
01:33:52.916 --> 01:33:55.083
How does this make sure
we're not hit again?

1478
01:33:55.958 --> 01:33:58.333
When I woke up this morning.
we were certain

1479
01:33:58.833 --> 01:34:01.500
the North Koreans
could not launch from a sub.

1480
01:34:01.583 --> 01:34:03.250
Now maybe they can. What the fuck?

1481
01:34:03.333 --> 01:34:05.791
The plan assumes
our target list is incomplete.

1482
01:34:05.875 --> 01:34:08.458
But by taking out the most critical
command and control centers.

1483
01:34:08.541 --> 01:34:09.625
it lowers the chance…

1484
01:34:09.708 --> 01:34:13.083
Or it provokes one. right?

1485
01:34:14.291 --> 01:34:15.333
Um…

1486
01:34:16.333 --> 01:34:20.375
My job is to explain your options and
execute your orders. I'm not qualified--

1487
01:34:20.458 --> 01:34:22.708
You carry this all day.
I've never seen it before.

1488
01:34:22.791 --> 01:34:25.875
It's like a fucking diner menu.
I'm asking for your help. son.

1489
01:34:29.541 --> 01:34:33.250
I actually call them
rare. medium. and well-done.

1490
01:34:35.500 --> 01:34:38.541
-It's sick. I know.
-Illustrates the point.

1491
01:34:40.166 --> 01:34:42.750
I sit still. Do nothing for now.

1492
01:34:43.250 --> 01:34:46.791
You can.
Hope this is a fluke or a one-off.

1493
01:34:46.875 --> 01:34:49.000
That whoever did this just stops.

1494
01:34:57.416 --> 01:34:58.916
God give you any answers?

1495
01:34:59.541 --> 01:35:00.458
Uh…

1496
01:35:00.958 --> 01:35:03.041
Not looking for one. sir. I just…

1497
01:35:04.083 --> 01:35:05.500
Sorry. sir.

1498
01:35:05.583 --> 01:35:07.958
Don't apologize. I go to church. I just…

1499
01:35:09.833 --> 01:35:11.333
I haven't for a while.

1500
01:35:13.208 --> 01:35:16.791
I always thought having you
follow me around with that book of plans

1501
01:35:16.875 --> 01:35:18.416
for weapons like that…

1502
01:35:18.916 --> 01:35:20.958
Just being ready is the point. right?

1503
01:35:21.041 --> 01:35:24.041
Keeps people in check.
Keeps the world straight.

1504
01:35:24.125 --> 01:35:28.750
If they see how prepared we are.
no one starts a nuclear war. right?

1505
01:35:29.250 --> 01:35:32.375
Like you said before. it's insanity.

1506
01:35:33.875 --> 01:35:35.125
But someone did.

1507
01:35:36.458 --> 01:35:37.958
So none of this makes sense.

1508
01:35:39.416 --> 01:35:40.875
Unless it was a mistake.

1509
01:35:40.958 --> 01:35:42.166
But the genie's out.

1510
01:35:42.833 --> 01:35:46.041
If we do nothing. the bad guys see
that they can get away with it.

1511
01:35:47.875 --> 01:35:49.500
I listened to this podcast.

1512
01:35:50.333 --> 01:35:52.125
and the guy said. uh.

1513
01:35:52.208 --> 01:35:55.875
"It's like we all built
a house filled with dynamite."

1514
01:35:57.166 --> 01:35:59.333
Making all these bombs
and all these plans. and

1515
01:35:59.833 --> 01:36:01.833
the walls are just ready to blow.

1516
01:36:02.416 --> 01:36:04.041
But we kept on living in it.

1517
01:36:14.000 --> 01:36:17.166
If you're gonna hit back. sir…

1518
01:36:20.375 --> 01:36:21.708
MAO7

1519
01:36:22.833 --> 01:36:24.083
or MAO9.

1520
01:36:25.458 --> 01:36:28.500
End it now. once and for all.

1521
01:36:29.833 --> 01:36:32.250
It's the best chance
some of us survive this.

1522
01:36:37.625 --> 01:36:40.166
<i>Mr. President.</i>
<i>we're going to need your decision.</i>

1523
01:36:40.833 --> 01:36:43.833
<i>Lieutenant Commander Reeves</i>
<i>is your strike advisor</i>

1524
01:36:44.541 --> 01:36:47.750
<i>and can walk you through</i>
<i>the authentication process.</i>

1525
01:36:47.833 --> 01:36:52.125
<i>Then you'll need to read aloud</i>
<i>an attack option designation.</i>

1526
01:36:56.958 --> 01:36:59.375
Reid. I need you…

1527
01:37:01.083 --> 01:37:02.291
What do you think. Reid?

1528
01:37:03.958 --> 01:37:05.333
Wait. Did we lose him?

1529
01:37:05.916 --> 01:37:08.833
Good morning. Mr. Secretary.
We're prepped and ready for takeoff.

1530
01:37:08.916 --> 01:37:10.458
Sir. where are you going?

1531
01:37:11.041 --> 01:37:12.625
No. no. no. no. no. sir!

1532
01:37:13.166 --> 01:37:14.333
Holy shit!

1533
01:37:14.916 --> 01:37:16.083
What was that?

1534
01:37:17.375 --> 01:37:21.500
<i>Mr. President?</i>
<i>It's Jake. uh. again. sir. Uh. Baerington.</i>

1535
01:37:21.583 --> 01:37:23.791
<i>I just spoke</i>
<i>to the Russian foreign minister.</i>

1536
01:37:23.875 --> 01:37:27.041
<i>He denies their responsibility</i>
<i>for the launch.</i>

1537
01:37:27.833 --> 01:37:31.375
<i>Said he spoke to Beijing.</i>
<i>and he doesn't think it was them either.</i>

1538
01:37:33.500 --> 01:37:36.000
<i>-I believed him. sir.</i>
-You did?

1539
01:37:37.500 --> 01:37:38.541
They gonna back down?

1540
01:37:38.625 --> 01:37:40.541
<i>Sir. I think</i>
<i>that they want to.</i>

1541
01:37:41.625 --> 01:37:44.166
<i>And if we can guarantee</i>
<i>that we will not retaliate.</i>

1542
01:37:44.250 --> 01:37:45.750
<i>I think I can. uh…</i>

1543
01:37:47.208 --> 01:37:49.583
<i>we can convince them.</i>

1544
01:37:49.666 --> 01:37:52.291
- What… what does that mean?
<i>- That we don't launch.</i>

1545
01:37:52.791 --> 01:37:54.041
<i>Against anyone.</i>

1546
01:37:54.750 --> 01:37:55.833
<i>For now. at least.</i>

1547
01:37:55.916 --> 01:37:58.666
So we just sit back
and watch Chicago incinerate?

1548
01:37:59.250 --> 01:38:02.500
Are you kidding me? Do you think
the American people are gonna go for that?

1549
01:38:02.583 --> 01:38:05.625
<i>Sir. the… the warhead.</i>
<i>it might still malfunction.</i>

1550
01:38:05.708 --> 01:38:07.166
<i>They do that sometimes.</i>

1551
01:38:07.250 --> 01:38:09.833
Did he agree to these terms?

1552
01:38:10.333 --> 01:38:13.166
All right. we do nothing.
they back off for certain?

1553
01:38:13.250 --> 01:38:15.000
- <i>More or less.</i>
- More or less?!

1554
01:38:15.708 --> 01:38:17.291
- Jake.
<i>- Yes. sir.</i>

1555
01:38:17.375 --> 01:38:19.125
I'm gonna need you to breathe.

1556
01:38:19.208 --> 01:38:20.458
<i>I'm breathing fine.</i>

1557
01:38:20.541 --> 01:38:23.916
Good 'cause my job is
to make this decision. I wish it weren't.

1558
01:38:24.416 --> 01:38:27.833
And your job is to tell me
exactly what he agreed to.

1559
01:38:28.458 --> 01:38:29.458
All right?

1560
01:38:30.208 --> 01:38:33.000
- No bullshit. Can you do that?
<i>- He didn't agree to anything.</i>

1561
01:38:33.083 --> 01:38:34.958
<i>He said he needed</i>
<i>to speak with his president.</i>

1562
01:38:35.541 --> 01:38:37.833
<i>Sounds to me</i>
<i>like we know nothing new.</i>

1563
01:38:37.916 --> 01:38:39.166
<i>Wrong. General.</i>

1564
01:38:39.250 --> 01:38:40.666
<i>If we do what he's asking.</i>

1565
01:38:40.750 --> 01:38:42.916
<i>if we hold back.</i>
<i>there's at least a chance.</i>

1566
01:38:43.000 --> 01:38:44.750
<i>Two minutes and 30 seconds.</i>

1567
01:38:44.833 --> 01:38:50.166
Jake. I do what you're suggesting.
I let whoever did this get away with it.

1568
01:38:50.916 --> 01:38:52.875
How is that any different
from surrendering?

1569
01:38:52.958 --> 01:38:54.916
<i>Sir.</i>
<i>if you wanna look at it that way.</i>

1570
01:38:55.666 --> 01:38:57.833
<i>then I'm telling you your choices are</i>

1571
01:38:57.916 --> 01:38:59.708
<i>surrender or suicide.</i>

1572
01:39:09.750 --> 01:39:11.125
I'm gonna need a minute.

1573
01:39:29.125 --> 01:39:30.291
Yes. sir.

1574
01:39:30.375 --> 01:39:31.666
- Ma'am.
- Yeah.

1575
01:39:31.750 --> 01:39:33.458
It's the president. Sounds urgent.

1576
01:39:37.083 --> 01:39:39.000
Hey. hon. Is everything okay?

1577
01:39:41.166 --> 01:39:42.166
What?

1578
01:39:49.166 --> 01:39:50.666
Did you say nuclear?

1579
01:39:51.458 --> 01:39:52.958
Oh my God.

1580
01:39:54.333 --> 01:39:56.083
Oh my God. I don't know.

1581
01:40:00.541 --> 01:40:02.333
They want me to retaliate.

1582
01:40:04.041 --> 01:40:08.291
It's a lot of lives. A lot of lives.
And if I don't…

1583
01:40:11.541 --> 01:40:12.708
Are you there?

1584
01:40:14.291 --> 01:40:15.458
Are you there?

1585
01:40:16.083 --> 01:40:17.083
Ali.

1586
01:40:18.000 --> 01:40:19.500
<i>Can you get him back?</i>

1587
01:40:20.333 --> 01:40:21.916
- Alison.
<i>- I…</i>

1588
01:40:22.000 --> 01:40:23.000
You did what?

1589
01:40:23.625 --> 01:40:25.041
This fucking…

1590
01:40:37.125 --> 01:40:38.375
All right. I'm here.

1591
01:40:39.083 --> 01:40:41.500
- You'll need your SAS card. sir.
- Oh.

1592
01:40:47.708 --> 01:40:48.708
Right.

1593
01:40:49.458 --> 01:40:51.291
Reminds me of when I was in college.

1594
01:40:54.291 --> 01:40:56.666
You just. uh. read it aloud.

1595
01:40:59.083 --> 01:41:01.833
November. Delta. Oscar.

1596
01:41:02.416 --> 01:41:05.583
One. one. one. seven.

1597
01:41:05.666 --> 01:41:08.541
- <i>November. Delta. Oscar.</i>
- Let me see that.

1598
01:41:08.625 --> 01:41:10.958
<i>One. one. one. seven.</i>

1599
01:41:12.875 --> 01:41:15.166
<i>National command authority confirmed.</i>

1600
01:41:16.833 --> 01:41:18.666
<i>Your orders. Mr. President?</i>

1601
01:41:19.416 --> 01:41:20.583
My orders?

1602
01:41:30.041 --> 01:41:32.708
Joe! Joe. come on! Joe!

1603
01:41:40.708 --> 01:41:42.708
- Form a line.
- Get your IDs out.

1604
01:41:42.791 --> 01:41:44.250
Keep it orderly. folks.

1605
01:41:44.333 --> 01:41:45.916
Keep moving. man.

1606
01:41:46.000 --> 01:41:47.916
Have your IDs ready.

1607
01:41:48.000 --> 01:41:49.916
Bus three is full! Send it!

1608
01:41:50.833 --> 01:41:52.250
Room for two more on seven.

1609
01:41:53.750 --> 01:41:56.416
- Sorry. she's not on the list.
- This way. Come on.

1610
01:41:56.916 --> 01:41:58.625
Keep it orderly. folks!

1611
01:41:59.791 --> 01:42:02.750
- Bus four is ready. Send it.
- Get your IDs out.

1612
01:42:03.875 --> 01:42:05.333
Have your IDs ready.
